US Descr Str: A menacing skull with crossed swords, the symbol\nof the Air Pirates. Increases Magic Resistance.
Crafted after a mystical red bird, and decorated\nwith red feathers. Increases Magic Resistance.
A sculpture based on the mythical guardian of\nPyrynn. Increases Magic Resistance.
A sculpture of an arcwhale, the guardian of the\nskies. Increases Magic Resistance.
A sculpture of a Quetya, an Ixa'takan Deity.\nIts divine power increases Magic Resistance.
A sculpture in the form of a giant.\nIncreases Magic Resistance.
A sculpture of Bluheim, the Yafutoman Gigas.\nIncreases Magic Resistance.
A sculpture of the goddess of love, courage,\nand victory. Increases Magic Resistance.
A shameless sculpture of Vyse. \nIncreases Magic Resistance.
A glowing sphere.\nIncreases Magic Resistance.
Protects the ship's engine from getting dirty,\nand increases the ship's speed.
Ship Modification, that increases the Moon Stone\npower output, increasing the ship's speed.
A kit that increases engine size for greater\npower and exhaust, increasing ship speed.
An additional propeller that increases the\nship's speed.
Sends clean air into the engine, stabilizing\nfuel consumption and increasing ship speed.
A compound turbo kit that modifies the engine\nand gives the ship more speed.
Standardizes valve timing to stabilize engine\nexhaust, increasing ship speed.
A triple turbo kit for maximum engine power, for\na speed boost even greater than the Twin Turbo.
Raises durability for greater power through\nhigher RPM's, increasing ship speed.
Splits the engine into two independent stages,\ndoubling power output and increasing ship speed.
A standard armored deck, commonly available.\nImproves ship defense.
A deck armored with multiple layers of steel.\nHas high defensive power.
Deflects projectiles with slanted plates atop\na standard armored deck. Improves ship defense.
A deck armored with layers of different steels.\nHas high defensive power.
A deck with armor three times as thick as the\nstandard weight. Improves ship defense.
A deck armored with an alloy including Moonstone\ndust. Improves ship defense.
An armored deck created by Yafutoman craftsmen.\nBeautiful and greatly improves ship defenses.
A deck armored with a rare, mysterious metal\nfrom ancient times. Improves ship defense.
An armored deck supplemented with high grade\nMoonstones. Their power improves ship defense.
An armored deck studded with Moonstones of 6\ndifferent colors. Improves ship defense.
A system for communicating between decks. \nGood luck keeping Aika from abusing it.
State-of-the-art cooking facilities for great-\ntasting dinners every night.
Takes advantage of engine heat to keep\nliving quarters nice and comfortable.
Purifies the air below decks to keep everything\nsmelling clean and fresh, not sweaty.
A bit of Yaftoman culture to help calm the mind\nand soothe the soul.
Blocks annoying engine noise for a better\nnight's sleep, reducing fatigue on long trips.
A custom-made wheel, ergonomically designed in\nValua. Reduces fatigue for the helmsman.
Luxurious lighting favored by Valuan nobility.\nBrings a touch of opulence to airborne life.
A carved wooden doll, shaped like a cuddly\nanimal. Simple, cute, and adored by Fina.
Some greenery to provide color aboard the ship.\nHas a soothing effect, and helps clean the air.
